<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="287" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1038,1891]" pageId="2" pageNumber="287">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,212,1038,1063]" pageId="2" pageNumber="287">Male</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[227,346,1038,1063]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 7 – 10" captionStart-1="FIGURES 11 – 12" captionStart-2="FIGURE 13" captionStart-3="FIGURES 14" captionStartId-0="4.[151,264,1684,1707]" captionStartId-1="5.[151,264,1457,1480]" captionStartId-2="6.[151,250,1723,1745]" captionStartId-3="7.[151,264,1725,1748]" captionTargetBox-0="[164,1405,211,1645]" captionTargetBox-1="[170,1417,211,1417]" captionTargetBox-2="[151,1436,193,1701]" captionTargetBox-3="[367,1220,214,1684]" captionTargetId-0="figure@4.[152,1434,193,1663]" captionTargetId-1="figure@5.[151,1436,193,1437]" captionTargetId-2="figure@6.[151,1436,193,1701]" captionTargetId-3="figure@7.[340,1248,193,1704]" captionTargetPageId-0="4" captionTargetPageId-1="5" captionTargetPageId-2="6" captionTargetPageId-3="7" captionText-0="FIGURES 7 – 10. Mesocapnia daxingana, sp. nov. 7. Male head and pronotum, dorsal view; 8. Male terminalia, dorsal view; 9. Male terminalia, lateral view; 10. Male terminalia, ventral view." captionText-1="FIGURES 11 – 12. Mesocapnia daxingana, sp. nov. 11. Main epiproct sclerite, dorsal view; 12. Main epiproct sclerite apex, dorsal view." captionText-2="FIGURE 13. Mesocapnia daxingana, sp. nov. Male habitus, dorsal view." captionText-3="FIGURES 14. Comparison between epiprocts of M. variabilis, M. gorodkovi and M. daxingana sp. nov. (upper three in dorsal view, lower three in lateral view)." httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/259620/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/259621/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/259622/files/figure.png" httpUri-3="https://zenodo.org/record/259623/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="287">Figs. 7–14</figureCitation>
). Body length 4.5–4.6 mm. Wings slightly brachypterous and subhyaline, veins brown. Forewing length 3.2–3.4 mm, hindwing length 2.6–2.7 mm. Body generally dark brown. Antennae slender, approximately same length as forewing. Pronotum with dark rugosities, mesometanota with pair of depressions posteromedially (
<figureCitation box="[159,231,1146,1171]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 10" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1684,1707]" captionTargetBox="[164,1405,211,1645]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[152,1434,193,1663]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 10. Mesocapnia daxingana, sp. nov. 7. Male head and pronotum, dorsal view; 8. Male terminalia, dorsal view; 9. Male terminalia, lateral view; 10. Male terminalia, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259620/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="287">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
). Mesothoracic postfurcasternal plates separated from spinasternum. Terga 1–9 with a pale longitudinal stripe, terga 4–9 with sclerotized anterior margins, tergum 10 with a medial membranous area and a posteromedial indentation (
<figureCitation box="[294,374,1218,1243]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 10" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1684,1707]" captionTargetBox="[164,1405,211,1645]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[152,1434,193,1663]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 10. Mesocapnia daxingana, sp. nov. 7. Male head and pronotum, dorsal view; 8. Male terminalia, dorsal view; 9. Male terminalia, lateral view; 10. Male terminalia, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259620/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="287">Figs. 8</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[389,420,1219,1243]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1723,1745]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1701]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,193,1701]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 13. Mesocapnia daxingana, sp. nov. Male habitus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259622/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="287">13</figureCitation>
). Main epiproct sclerite reflexed, reaching middle of tergum 9, broad and nearly parallel sided in dorsal view; posterior portion slightly narrowed from broad base, gradually narrowed to anterior 1/6 then abruptly tapering to a sharp, apicomedian spine; spine with distinct dorsomedial groove (
<figureCitation box="[1156,1264,1290,1315]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 10" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1684,1707]" captionTargetBox="[164,1405,211,1645]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[152,1434,193,1663]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 10. Mesocapnia daxingana, sp. nov. 7. Male head and pronotum, dorsal view; 8. Male terminalia, dorsal view; 9. Male terminalia, lateral view; 10. Male terminalia, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259620/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="287">Figs. 8–9</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1277,1349,1291,1315]" captionStart="FIGURES 11 – 12" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1457,1480]" captionTargetBox="[170,1417,211,1417]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,193,1437]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 11 – 12. Mesocapnia daxingana, sp. nov. 11. Main epiproct sclerite, dorsal view; 12. Main epiproct sclerite apex, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259621/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="287">11–12</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1361,1392,1291,1315]" captionStart="FIGURES 14" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1725,1748]" captionTargetBox="[367,1220,214,1684]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[340,1248,193,1704]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 14. Comparison between epiprocts of M. variabilis, M. gorodkovi and M. daxingana sp. nov. (upper three in dorsal view, lower three in lateral view)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259623/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="287">14</figureCitation>
). In lateral aspect, main epiproct sclerite curved, tubular but slightly constricted at 1/3 distance from base to apex (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 10" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1684,1707]" captionTargetBox="[164,1405,211,1645]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[152,1434,193,1663]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 10. Mesocapnia daxingana, sp. nov. 7. Male head and pronotum, dorsal view; 8. Male terminalia, dorsal view; 9. Male terminalia, lateral view; 10. Male terminalia, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259620/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="287">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[188,219,1363,1387]" captionStart="FIGURES 14" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1725,1748]" captionTargetBox="[367,1220,214,1684]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[340,1248,193,1704]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 14. Comparison between epiprocts of M. variabilis, M. gorodkovi and M. daxingana sp. nov. (upper three in dorsal view, lower three in lateral view)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259623/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="287">14</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plate semi-elliptical with sclerotized margins (
<figureCitation box="[948,1040,1362,1387]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 10" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1684,1707]" captionTargetBox="[164,1405,211,1645]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[152,1434,193,1663]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 10. Mesocapnia daxingana, sp. nov. 7. Male head and pronotum, dorsal view; 8. Male terminalia, dorsal view; 9. Male terminalia, lateral view; 10. Male terminalia, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259620/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="287">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
). Cerci slender with long hairs, approaching forewing length.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1038,1891]" box="[199,418,1434,1459]" pageId="2" pageNumber="287">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,293,1434,1459]" pageId="2" pageNumber="287">Female.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
